6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to public nuisance; amending 50 O.S.
2021, Sections 2, which relates to public nuisance
8 definition; prohibiting certain finding; amending 50
O.S. 2021, Section 8, which relates to remedies;
9 clarifying remedies; requiring certain finding;
amending 50 O.S. 2021, Section 10, which relates to
10 cause of action; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 2, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 2. A public nuisance is one which affects at the same
17 time an entire community or neighborhood, or any considerable number
18 of persons, although the extent of the annoyance or damage inflicted
19 upon the individuals may be unequal. The manufacturing, marketing,
20 or selling of lawful products cannot be deemed a public nuisance.
21 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 8, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 Section 8. A. The remedies against a public nuisance
24 are:
Req. No. 10586 Page 1

1 1. Indictment or information, or;
2 2. A civil action, or seeking injunctive or other equitable
3 relief; or
4 3. Abatement;.
5 B. To be found liable in an action for public nuisance, the
6 defendant in such action must be determined by the judge to have
7 been in control of the conditions giving rise to the public nuisance
8 at the time of injury.
9 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 50 O.S. 2021, Section 10, is
10 amended to read as follows:
11 Section 10. A private person may maintain an action for a
12 public nuisance if it is specially injurious to himself the judge
13 determines by clear and convincing evidence the public nuisance is
14 the proximate cause of special injury to the private person, but not
15 otherwise.
16 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
